  "prompt": "Which is best 2 in 1 laptop under Rs 25000?",
  "response": "Finding a good 2-in-1 laptop under Rs 25,000 is quite challenging due to budget constraints. Most 2-in-1 laptops (convertible laptops) in this price range may have limited performance, build quality, or features. However, here are a couple of options you can consider within this budget:\n\n### 1. **Lenovo IdeaPad Flex 5i (Refurbished)**\n   - **Display**: 14-inch HD touchscreen\n   - **Processor**: Intel Pentium Silver or Celeron\n   - **RAM**: 4GB\n   - **Storage**: 128GB SSD\n   - **Features**: Convertible design, lightweight, and portable\n   - **Price**: Around Rs 24,000 (refurbished models)\n   - **Note**: Refurbished laptops can be a good option if you\u2019re looking for better specifications within a budget.\n\n### 2. **Dell Inspiron 3195 (Refurbished)**\n   - **Display**: 11.6-inch HD touchscreen\n   - **Processor**: AMD A6 or A9\n   - **RAM**: 4GB\n   - **Storage**: 128GB SSD\n   - **Features**: Compact and lightweight, comes with a stylus\n   - **Price**: Around Rs 22,000-25,000 (refurbished models)\n\n### 3. **Acer Spin 1 (Refurbished)**\n   - **Display**: 11.6-inch HD touchscreen\n   - **Processor**: Intel Celeron or Pentium\n   - **RAM**: 4GB\n   - **Storage**: 64GB eMMC\n   - **Features**: Portable and affordable\n   - **Price**: Around Rs 23,000 (refurbished models)\n\n### Points to Keep in Mind:\n1. **Refurbished Models**: Since new 2-in-1 laptops under Rs 25,000 are rare, refurbished models can be a cost-effective option. Ensure you buy from a trusted seller with a warranty.\n2. **Specifications**: Lower-end processors like Intel Celeron, Pentium, or AMD A6/A9 are sufficient for basic tasks like browsing, document editing, and media consumption but not for heavy workloads.\n3. **Storage**: eMMC storage is slower than SSDs, so consider this when making your choice.\n\n### Alternative Option:\nIf you can stretch your budget slightly (around Rs 30,000), you\u2019ll find better options like the **HP Pavilion x360** or **Lenovo Flex 5** with improved performance and build quality.\n\n**Tip**: Check local deals, sales, or offline stores for better prices on refurbished or older models.",
